e is mislabeled an arson. Corrupt police plant drugs on an innocent suspect. A false allegation of assault is invented to resolve a custody dispute. With this book, former New York City public defender Jessica S. Henry sheds essential light on a deeply flawed criminal justice system that allows-even encourages-these convictions to regularly occur. Smoke but No Fire promises to be eye-opening reading for legal professionals, students, activists, and the general public alike as it grapples with the chilling reality that far too many innocent people spend real years behind bars for fictional crimes.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aFalse imprisonmentzUnited States. 0aJudicial errorzUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh  aconviction.  acops.  acrime.  acriminal justice system.  aexoneration.  aeyewitnesses.  aflawed.  aforensic experts.  ainformants.  ainnocence.  alaw.  alies.  aplanted evidence.  apolice.  apractical solutions.  aproblematic.  areform.  awrongful imprisonment.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2020 Englishz978311070472308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Sociology, Education, Psychology 2020z9783110704549oZDB-23-SEW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020z978311069041540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520971943zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520971943423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520971943.jpg  a978-3-11-069041-5  UC Press Frontlist eBook-Package 2020